ions of the complex social and economic forces shaping our cities today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnterprise zonesxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aEnterprise zoneszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aGentrificationxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aGentrificationzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aHousing policyxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aHousing policyzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aLatin AmericansxHousingxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aLatin AmericansxHousingxUnited States. 0aLatin AmericansxHousingzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aLatin AmericansxHousingzUnited States. 0aPuerto RicansxHousingxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aPuerto RicansxHousingzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aUrban developmentxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aUrban developmentzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aUrbanizationzNew York (State)zNew York. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  aamerican legislation.  acharter schools.  aclass differences.  aconsumption.  acultural politics.  ademographic studies.  aeconomic empowerment.  ael barrio.  aethnic issues.  agentrification.  aglobalization.  ahousing crises.  aimmigrant experience.  ainterethnic relations.  alargest minority group.  alatinization.  alatinos.  aneoliberals.  anew york.  anonfiction.  apuerto ricans.  aracial issues.  asociology.  aspanish harlem.  atextbooks.  aurban landscape.  aurban space.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093772740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937727423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937727/